reviews.text: kind service, delicious food. especially Korean style sasimi good.

This restaurant has been operating over 25(maybe 30) years, and the boss is really kind. The food was really good and I specially liked Kimchi stew and BBQ. Food prices are not expensive, and set menus are value for money. You can count on it!
Wonderful atmosphere. Warm service! One of the most authentic experience for Korean food. Place has been around for a long time and many long time customers return to eat there.

lunch set in good value。。。hot tea。。。many students from St.Mary 。。like you are in a school canteen with students。。。

the boss is around cooking or serving。。。。she is with great manner。。。。
A real Korean restaurant serving traditional Korean food, unlike the deep fried chicken places...
